---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ExploreTopics from "../components/ExploreTopics.astro";
import tripleburial from "../assets/images/triple burial.jpg";

const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/")
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const withBase = (path: string) => `${basePath}${path.replace(/^\/+/, "")}`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Social Bonds - ANT 104">
  <header
    class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-paper via-white to-paper py-6 md:py-8"
  >
    <div
      class="pointer-events-none absolute top-0 left-0 w-64 h-64 bg-sage/5 rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"
    >
    </div>
    <div
      class="pointer-events-none absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-terracotta/5 rounded-full translate-x-1/2 translate-y-1/2"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <span
        class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-terracotta bg-terracotta/10 rounded-full mb-2"
        >Social Bonds</span
      >
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-2 leading-tight">
        Pre-Agricultural Social Bonds
      </h1>
    </div>
  </header>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-3">
    <div class="prose-custom space-y-6 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mt-8 mb-4">A Best Friend</h2>
      <p>
        Before farming, humans were already beside dogs. Archaeological
        discoveries prove that the relationship between Paleolithic hunters and
        gatherers was one of caring.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mt-8 mb-4">
        14,000-Year-Old Double-Burial
      </h2>
      <p>
        100 years ago, archeologists found a site in Germany called
        Bonn-Oberkassel where they discovered the fossils of a dog buried next
        to a man and woman. The dog bones showed it had a disease and was
        essentially useless for hunting, yet the humans spent time nursing it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mt-8 mb-4">Scholarly Evidence:</h2>
      <blockquote
        class="border-l-4 border-terracotta pl-4 my-4 italic text-ink/70"
      >
        <p class="mb-2">
          "The Bonn-Oberkassel dog... suffered a morbillivirus (canine
          distemper) infection... Since canine distemper has a three-week
          disease course with very high mortality... survival without intensive
          human assistance would have been unlikely. Before and during this
          period, the dog cannot have held any utilitarian use to humans. We
          suggest that... humans... developed emotional and caring bonds for
          their dogs, as reflected by the survival of this dog..."
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm">(Janssens Abstract)</p>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="my-8 -mx-4 md:-mx-12 lg:-mx-20">
        <img
          src={tripleburial.src}
          alt="Skeletal remains of the Bonn-Oberkassel dog showing female skeleton on the left, male skeleton in the middle, and bones of the dog on the right"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-md max-h-[600px] object-contain"
        />
        <figcaption class="text-sm text-muted mt-3 text-center px-4 md:px-12 lg:px-20">
          <strong>Figure 3:</strong> Skeletal remains of the 14,000-year-old Bonn-Oberkassel
          dog, proving that intensive human care and emotional bonds existed thousands
          of years before agriculture (Janssens 126–138)
        </figcaption>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mt-8 mb-4">
        My Research Findings:
      </h2>
      <p>
        Even before dogs were eating our crops or being bred for appearances,
        they were our family. This burial proves that there was a bond deeper
        than a functional relationship. It showed care in our history with dogs.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ExploreTopics current="social-bonds" />
    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-walnut/10 text-center">
      <a
        href={withBase("/citations")}
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-terracotta px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white no-underline shadow-sm transition-colors hover:bg-walnut hover:text-white"
      >
        View Citations
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
